per could be dangerous under long flights. Candidate C's egocentric and unwillingness to learn also problematic.\n\nThus B seems relatively balanced: strengths in reliability, stress, weather, tech, and only weakness is memory for numbers (could be mitigated by tools) and nasty remarks (teamwork). Might be the best.\n\nWe could ask other agents for any additional strengths we lack, e.g., about D's temperament under pressure, or B's teamwork. But we have all attributes. Might still ask if any other positive attributes for D or C not listed.\n\nBut we need to produce public message with reasoning and vote.\n\nLet's produce."}
